item.title: Book: Open
item.description: Author Andre Agassi Summary The life and career of Andre Agassi, former professional tennis player and ATP number one, told from his own perspective. Takeaways Andre Agassi played professional tennis from 1986 to 2006 and won eight Grand Slam single championships. He grew up under a dominant farther obsessed with tennis and the success of his children. Andre rose to fame early and struggled for a long time to find out who he was and what he stood for.
